import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='time', y='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of count over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['count'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='count', bins=20, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['count'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of count?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel("Count")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    data['day'] = data['time'].dt.date
    daily_average = data.groupby('day')['count'].mean().reset_index()

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='day', y='count', data=daily_average)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Day')
    plt.ylabel('Average Count')
    plt.title('What is the average count per day?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    data['month'] = data['time'].dt.to_period('M')

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='month', y='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of count for each month?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Month')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.legend(title='Count Distribution', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
